sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant MutWebhook as Mutating Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant ValWebhook as Validating Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Operator as KubeRay Operator
    participant HeadPod as Ray Head Pod<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant WorkerPods as Ray Worker Pods
    participant Gateway as Platform Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KubeRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant CertMgr as cert-manager<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Redis as Redis<br/>6379/TCP

    Note over User,Redis: Flow 1: RayCluster Provisioning

    User->>K8sAPI: POST RayCluster CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>MutWebhook: Mutate RayCluster<br/>TLS, API server cert
    MutWebhook-->>K8sAPI: Set secure-trusted-network=true<br/>Disable enableIngress
    K8sAPI->>ValWebhook: Validate RayCluster<br/>TLS, API server cert
    ValWebhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation result<br/>(DNS name, unique workers)
    K8sAPI-->>User: RayCluster created

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch RayCluster events<br/>ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Head Pod<br/>ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods<br/>ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Head Service<br/>ServiceAccount token

    Note over User,Redis: Flow 2: RayJob Submission (HTTP Mode)

    User->>K8sAPI: POST RayJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Operator->>HeadPod: Submit job via Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP (cluster-internal)
    loop Poll status
        Operator->>HeadPod: GET job status<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    end
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update RayJob status

    Note over User,Redis: Flow 3: Authenticated Dashboard Access (RHOAI)

    User->>Gateway: HTTPS request<br/>443/TCP TLS 1.2+, OIDC token
    Gateway->>KubeRBAC: HTTPRoute forwarding<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    KubeRBAC->>K8sAPI: TokenReview<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA token
    K8sAPI-->>KubeRBAC: Token valid
    KubeRBAC->>HeadPod: Proxy to Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP (localhost)
    HeadPod-->>KubeRBAC: Dashboard response
    KubeRBAC-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>User: Dashboard content

    Note over User,Redis: Flow 4: mTLS Certificate Provisioning

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Issuer CR<br/>ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Certificate CR<br/>ServiceAccount token
    CertMgr->>K8sAPI: Issue TLS Secret<br/>(CA -> head/worker certs)
    Note over HeadPod: Init container waits for<br/>TLS Secret with pod IP SAN
    HeadPod->>WorkerPods: Ray protocol<br/>10001/TCP mTLS (CA-signed certs)
